(602, 120, 'descrip', '<h2>Step 1</h2>\r\n<p>Cut the bacon into small pieces and cook over medium heat just until crisp; drain on paper towels.<p/>\r\n<h2>Step 2</h2>\r\n<p>Bring a large saucepan of salted water to a boil. Add the broccoli and blanch until bright green and slightly softened, about 3 minutes. Drain well, run under cold water to stop the cooking, and drain again.<p/>\r\n<h2>Step 3</h2>\r\n<p>IIn a mixing bowl, combine the mayonnaise, vinegar, onion, sugar and raisins. Add the broccoli and toss the coat with the dressing. Refrigerate for 1 hour.<p/>\r\n<h2>Step 4</h2>\r\n<p>Just before servings, fold in the sunflower kernels and the bacon pieces. Serve immediately.<p/>'),
