(628, 119, 'descrip', '<h2>Step 1</h2>\r\n<p>Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F.<p/>\r\n<h2>Step 2</h2>\r\n<p>Season salmon with salt and pepper. Place salmon, skin side down, on a non-stick baking sheet or in a non-stick pan with an oven-proof handle. Bake until salmon is cooked through, about 12 to 15 minutes. Serve with the Toasted Almond Parsley Salad and squash, if desired.<p/>\r\n<h2>Step 3</h2>\r\n<p>Mince the shallot and add to a small bowl. Pour the vinegar over the shallots and add a pinch of salt. Let sit for 30 minutes.<p/>\r\n<h2>Step 4</h2>\r\n<p>Roughly chop the capers, parsley and almonds and add to the shallots. Add the olive oil, tasting as you go. Mix again and adjust the seasonings.<p/>'),
